    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-04-27T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-04-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="396"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 396</seg>
                </opener>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.10/4–2551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Spain</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d396fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_DWB1"
                            >Dunham</persName> and cleared with Sauer of the Export-Import Bank,
                            <persName corresp="#p_CJC2">Corbett</persName> of the Office of
                        Financial and Development Policy, and Tannenwald of the Office of the
                        Special Assistant to the President, <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Averell
                            Harriman</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-04-27T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 27, 1951—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>741. Urtel 958 Apr 25.<note n="2" xml:id="d396fn2">Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="#p_GS1">Griffis</persName> had asked in this telegram if the
                        $25 million loan limitation with respect to Spain was still in effect and
                        added that it appeared that the Spanish Government knew nothing of this
                        limitation. (852.10/4–2551)</note> Carry-over to next fiscal year of funds
                    for loans to Spain suggested and approved by Pres. Ltr and doc re this action
                    has been air pouched to you. This info shld not be communicated in any form to
                    Spans. After admin steps have been taken to carry out action approved by Pres,
                    you will be instructed re informing Spans.</p>
                <p>Action re removing limitation being taken and it is therefore unnecessary you
                    communicate directly with Pres this subj.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
